<pre><code class="language-python">ship_img = pygame.image.load(&quot;ship.png&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> the picture file must be saved in the <strong>same folder</strong> as your code, with the exact name. Also use <code>.convert_alpha()</code> so the see-through background stays see-through.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — The high score should remember your best across rounds, but it resets to 0 every restart.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">if event.key == pygame.K_r and game_over:
    high_score = 0
    score = 0
    game_over = False
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> before resetting, compare the score to the best so far.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
